article.headline: Tennessee Tech 78, Wisconsin-Milwaukee 68
article.story: MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Anthony Fisher scored 17 points and Belton Rivers added 16 to lead Tennessee Tech to a 78-68 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Sunday night. Tennessee Tech (2-2) took the lead from the Panthers 50-47 on a 3-pointer by Rivers midway through the second half. Milwaukee (2-5) pulled to within two at 66-64 when Paige Paulsen, who finished with a team-high 13 points, hit 2-of-3 free throws with 2:48 remaining. But Tennessee Tech pulled away in the final minutes. Milwaukee led before the game even began after Paulsen hit 1-of-2 free throws prior to the tip because Tech was assessed a bench technical foul for dunking during warmups. But the Golden Eagles went on a 17-4 first-half run and took a 34-30 lead at halftime. Allan Hanson and Charlie Swiggett scored 11 points each for Milwaukee, while Amadi McKenzie added 11 points for Tennessee Tech.
